<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11L5232/834</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Luther</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-08">April 8, 1937</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                                the receipt of your note of April 5 regarding the attitude of your
                                Government with respect to the so-called sabotage claims pending
                                before the Mixed Claims Commission, United States and Germany, and
                                to state that a copy of your note has been transmitted to the
                                American Agent with the request that he lay it before the Commission
                                for its consideration.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>[File copy not signed.]</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>